The Petroleum and Natural Gas Senior Staff Association of Nigeria (PENGASSAN) has elected National Officers to pilot its affairs. The election, which took place on Thursday 27th August 2020, was conducted during the Union’s 6th Triennial National Delegates’ Conference held in Abuja. Highlights of the conference was the election of members of the Central Working Committee (CWC) among whom is Comrade Festus Osifo, a staff of Total E&P, who was elected President. Other officials include Comrades Matthew Duru and Kelechi Ugwulo who were elected Deputy President and National Industrial Relations Officer (IRO) respectively. In his acceptance speech, shortly after the swearing-in ceremony, Comrade Osifo promised to make members’ welfare his primary focus. 